Date: 5/1/1892
Source: Inangahua Times
Author:
Vol / Page: 2
Edition:
Quote: It is said that most of the leading Conservatives have [been] receiving lessons in Court etiquette from an old white bait dredger, who was once a kitchen wolloper in a gentleman's residence in at Picadilly, and that they are now able to bow as elegantly as a spavi[ned] Turk.
